main event: A circular, bright object was observed by a civilian for about 5-10 seconds over Chicago, Illinois on March 7, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as having a whitish or metallic surface and tapering towards the opposite end., The object emitted no sound and had no visible tail or exhaust., The light of the object went out briefly before coming back on., The object was first observed from a building obstructed view., The sighting was made under clear weather conditions.
witness description: The observer was a 28-year-old civilian, details of which are redacted.
